    <string name="how_to_wifi_desc">This guide is designed to help users gain a better understanding of Wi-Fi use at Farmingdale State College. It will help those in need to gain a better understanding of how to set it up, what networks to connect to and how long sessions last.</string>
    <string name="how_to_connect_desc">You can connect to the Wi-Fi using your Farmingdale email and password via either the FSC_Secure or FSC_Wifi. FSC_Secure is the highest security and most secure connection and is therefore the preferred method. Connections are valid for 120 days or until a password change.</string>
    <string name="dealing_with_issues_desc"><![CDATA[Any issues with Wi-Fi should be directed <a href="mailto:helpdesk@farmingdale.edu">helpdesk@farmingdale.edu</a> and should include: \n • the error message you\'re receiving \n • your full name \n • Ram ID \n • your Farmingdale Username \n • the make and model of the device \n • the MAC address of the device]]></string>
